COPY public.restaurants (restaurant_id, restaurant_name, restaurant_icon, restaurant_description, restaurant_address, restaurant_latitude, restaurant_longitude, restaurant_state, food_type, episode_info) FROM stdin;
1	Sauce Boss Southern Kitchen	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/11/19/0/DV3417-shrimp-and-grits-with-blackened-spiced-butter_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1637343510614.jpeg	\nChef Julius' persistence and determination to use food to bring happiness to people has also brought him success. His early culinary lessons came from helping his grandmother and aunts cook while he was growing up. After attending culinary school, he opened Sauce Boss food truck in 2016, specializing in original recipes and mastering sauces made from scratch. In 2019 he was able to expand, bringing his enthusiasm and experience, and open his own restaurant serving Southern food that he learned how to make from his grandmother.\n	\n                  877 East 12300 South, Draper 84020	40.5271953	-111.866966	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
2	Graze	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/11/19/0/DV3417-vegan-chikn-bacon-ranch-club-sandwich_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1637343535993.jpeg	\nGraze is a family-owned, locally-sourced vegan restuarant. Their brunch and dinner menus offer many options for delicious plant-based dishes to be paired with a beverage from their drink menu.\n	\n                  1888 Eastland Ave, Nashville 37206	36.1824453	-86.7355728	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
3	'59er Diner and Cabins	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/11/19/0/DV3417-brown-gravy_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1637343501634.jpeg	\nStep back in time at this diner known for their milkshakes, all-day breakfast and '50s inspired theme, complete with a working jukebox and a decorated cabin for rent. Enjoy burgers, fries and meals off the griddle prepared with locally sourced eggs and produce.\n	\n                  15361 US 2 #9208, Leavenworth 98826	47.581006	-120.6143138	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
4	The Feisty Pint	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/11/17/0/DV3416_tims-roadkill-hash-2_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1637158779041.jpeg	\nThe Feisty Pint has traditional features of a pub: 26 beers on tap; mounted televisions; and bar fare like tacos, burgers, wings and fries. However, if you're a feisty patron, you can attempt either of their food challenges: The Feisty Challenge Burger, three angus patties with spicy toppings, or the Roadkill Challenge, three pounds of tater tot hash topped with bacon, jalapeños, onions, cheese and eggs.\n\n	\n                  359 Colorado Ave, Grand Junction 81501	39.0660299	-108.566306	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
5	Santo Taco	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/11/17/0/DV3416_birria-tacos_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1637158788785.jpeg	\nOwners Claudia and Alfonso gained hands-on culinary experience working in restaurants and professional kitchens. When they opened their own establishment, they brought their knowledge of making traditional Mexican food, as well as the skills they developed within the food industry. In addition to a namesake taco, you can find burritos, quesadillas and nacho fries as Santo Taco.\n	\n                  910 900 W, Salt Lake City 84116	40.78898780000001	-111.9162708	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
6	Fattoush Cafe	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/11/17/0/DV3416_lamb-shank-2_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1637158817392.jpeg	\nFattoush's halal fare is made with olive oil, grains, vegetables and meats found in the Mediterranean region. They serve up classic Greek cuisine such as salad, falafel, gyros and baklava.\n	\n                  1716 Charlotte Avenue, Nashville, TN 37203	36.1584056	-86.7996424	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
7	Papito Moe's	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/10/28/DV3415__carne-frita-moe-fongo_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1635440065864.jpeg	\nPapito Moe's prides itself on its authentic Puerto Rican cuisine and its warm service. Whether you visit their restaurant or catch their food truck, they aim to serve delicious empanadillas, moe'fongo and rice bowls with a smile.\n	\n                  7786 S 5600 W Suite 101, West Jordan, UT 84081	40.6395081	-112.0245665	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
8	Dump City Dumplings	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/10/28/DV3415_Chinese-Style-Pork-Dumpling_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1635440065990.jpeg	\nYou can visit Dump City's restaurant or food cart to try one of their dumpling varieties, including Four Cheese Pizza, vegan Pad Thai and Chinese style Pork.\n	\n                  384 SW Upper Terrace Dr., Bend, OR 97703	44.04642399999999	-121.3109807	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
9	Nicky's Coal Fired	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/10/28/DV3415_Spaghetti-with-meatballs_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1635440066218.jpeg	\nNicky's uses locally sourced ingredients and a coal fired oven to give their Italian cuisine a fresh and unique taste. They offer pizza, pasta and meatballs, one of their specialties.\n	\n                  5026 Centennial Blvd., Nashville 37209	36.162462	-86.84871299999999	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
10	Riddim N Spice	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/10/22/DV3414_bbq-beef-jackfruit_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1634914510109.jpeg	\nInspired by their love for Caribbean food, Jamaican brothers Kamal Kalokoh and Rashean Conaway created Riddim N Spice for those craving a taste of island food. Their dishes including barbeque jerk jackfruit, snapper and peas and rice.\n\n	\n                  2116 Meharry Blvd., Nashville, TN 37208	36.1678822	-86.81069769999999	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
11	Arempa's	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/10/22/DV3414_Pulled-Pork-Patacon_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1634914509643.jpeg	\nArepas, empanadas, cachapa and pabellon are some of the Venezuelan fare you'll find at Arempa's, with some vegan options.\n	\n                  350 South State St., Salt Lake City, UT 84111	40.761619	-111.8886482	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
12	Rockin' Dave's Bagel Bistro	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/10/22/DV3414__jalapeno-bagels_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1634914510472.jpeg	\nDavid Flier, a lover of food and a lover of music, combined his loves to create Rockin' Dave's Bagel Bistro & Backstage Lounge. At this friendly, casual dining restaurant, patrons can customize a bagel order, choose from an extensive menu with vegan and gluten-free options or enjoy the surprise monthly special.\n	\n                  661 NE Greenwood Ave., Bend 97701	44.0596345	-121.296113	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
13	The Pit Room	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/10/14/DV3413_brisket-tacos_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1634235906143.jpeg	\nMichael Sambrooks and Bramwell Tripp put their shared passion for delicious food and years of culinary experience together to create The Pit Room. Their dishes feature homemade recipes, created and smoked from scratch. In addition to barbeque, the pair serve up (breakfast) tacos.\n	\n                  1201 Richmond Ave., Houston, TX 77006	29.7342056	-95.3940574	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
14	Soy Bistro	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/10/14/DV3413__spicy-bork-bulgogi_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1634235905928.jpeg	\nA family-owned and operated restaurant that serves Korean cuisine; their house favorites are Bibimbap, Gochujang Chicken and Spicy Pork Bulgogi. Kenji Ichikawa, patron-turned-(co)owner, says he loves the level of attention Soy Bistro gives to their cuisine and to their customers, pledging to uphold the standard.\n	\n                  5008 Maryland Way, Brentwood, TN 37027	36.0348465	-86.79296049999999	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
15	Once Upon A Thyme	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/10/14/DV3413_meatloaf-panini_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1634235906359.jpeg	\nThis quaint and cute restaurant serves lunch, with vegetarian and vegan options, in a friendly space that is also home to a retail store, a garden and office spaces. The dishes are made from scratch, with a few patrons can purchase for carry-out or learn to make for themselves through cooking classes offered at the restaurant.\n\n	\n                  1090 NW State Ave., Chehalis, Washington 98532	46.671021	-122.973593	testrestaurant_state0	testfood_type0	testepisode_info0
16	Mackinaw's Restaurant	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/09/29/DV3412_Pakistani-Oxtail-Curry_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1632949316032.jpeg	\nMackinaw's eclectic menu features dishes made from farm-to-table ingredients. Inspired by food from all over the map, some of their signature dishes are Duck Breast, Southwestern Braised Rabbit and Oxtail Pakistani Curry.\n	\n                  545 N Market Blvd #1, Chehalis 98532	46.6655556	-122.9708333	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
17	The Toasted Coconut	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/09/29/DV3412_Pork-Dumplings_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1632949316290.jpeg	\nInspired by island cuisine, Martin and Sara Stayer created The Toasted Coconut for a stay-cation culinary experience. The brunch and dinner menu feature tropical takes on curries, sandwiches and fish dishes.\n	\n                  1617 Richmond Ave., Houston, TX 77006	29.7341294	-95.4001929	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
19	NW Sausage and Deli	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/09/02/DV3411_House-Pastrami-on-Rye_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1630595833205.jpeg	\nNW Sausage and Deli is home to more than 20 original recipes for smoked meats. The meats are prepared Old World style and include sausage, jerky and pepperoni and can be paired with original brews on tap.\n	\n                  5945 Prather Rd SW, Centralia, WA 98531	46.7715548	-123.0074005	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
20	Matteo's Osteria	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/09/02/DV3411_Lamb-Shank-Osobucco_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1630595832716.jpeg	\nIn addition to its extensive wine menu (as every osteria should have), Matteo's Osteria has classic Italian fare such as salad, pizza and pasta with some vegan options.\n	\n                  161 Wailea Ike Pl, A107, Wailea 96753	20.6889729	-156.4352858	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
21	Be More Pacific	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/09/02/DV3411_Kare-Kare_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1630595833052.jpeg	\nBe More Pacific is all about Filipino tradition: their variety of dishes have been passed down through generations and infused with each chef's personal touch. Be More Pacific celebrates other aspects of Filipino culture, including hosting karaoke, a kamayan eating experience and a monthly Filipino-owned market.\n	\n                  506 Yale Street, Ste E, Houston, TX 77007	29.7801231	-95.39845389999999	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
22	Weights + Measures	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/08/30/DV3410_Roasted-Carrot-Pizza_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1630335277939.jpeg	\nHoused in a repurposed warehouse and the brainchild of four partners: a developer, a chef, a baker and a bartender; Weights + Measures is a casual restaurant, bakery and bar serving comfort food in a relaxed space.\n	\n                  2808 Caroline St., Houston, TX 77004	29.742625	-95.3727723	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
23	Fresco Cafe Italiano	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/08/30/DV3410_Spaghetti-alla-carbonara_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1630335278071.jpeg	\nChef Roberto Crescini trained in Italy, honing his culinary skills for decades before bringing them to Houston to serve a variety of made-to-order meals, including classic dishes like bolognese, lamb, pasta and pizza. At Fresco Cafe Italiano, patrons can expect authentic, fresh Italian dishes made in-house with ingredients imported from Italy.\n	\n                  3277 Southwest Fwy, Suite A, Houston 77027	29.7286485	-95.4317975	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
24	Joey's Kitchen	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/07/09/DV3407_Crispy-Pata_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1625849838280.jpeg	\nChef Joey Macadangdang is a student of Hawaiin culinary arts, as evidenced by his carefully and artfully prepared dishes made with fresh ingredients like fish, pork, okra, long beans and eggplant. The menu also reflects the Filipino, Chinese, Japanese and Portuguese flavors that inspire the food.\n	\n                  5095 Napilihau St., Lahaina 96761	20.9850372	-156.6674133	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
26	The Butcher Shop Beer Garden & Grill	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/08/06/DV3409__churrasco-steak-burger_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1628265312768.jpeg	\nIgor and Fred Niznik, a father-son duo, took on the creative challenge of opening a restaurant and combined their passion for food, beer and quality to transform a butcher shop into a dining hotspot. The full service butcher shop is still a feature of the restaurant; patrons can order cuts and all of the meat for the restaurarnt is cut in-house.\n	\n                  209 6th Street, West Palm Beach 33401	26.7191266	-80.0512068	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
41	Passage to India	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2020/29/DV3306_lamb-rogan-josh_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1609268557562.jpeg	\nPassage to India believes in sharing Indian cuisine in its most authentic form, meaning they retain all of the spice, flavor and originality found in traditional family-run eateries across India.\n	\n                  855 45th St. S, Suite A3, Fargo, ND 58103	46.86785500000001	-96.862757	testrestaurant_state2	testfood_type2	testepisode_info2
27	Cafe Pesto	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/08/06/DV3409__bolognese-pasta_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1628265312919.jpeg	\nCafe Pesto has it all - including seafood, breakfast and brunch, dessert and a selection of beverages. From their beginnings as a pizzeria (they have that too!) to their expansion of locally and historically inspired dishes prepared with care, Cafe Pesto seeks to create a dining experience that allows guests to "drift back in time awakened to the present only by the colorful and provocative meal presentations."\n	\n                  308 Kamehameha Ave #101, Hilo 96720	19.723735	-155.0850148	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
28	South Maui Fish Company	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/07/16/DV3408__Traditional-Poke-Bowl_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1626451744068.jpeg	\nSouth Maui Fish Company believes in a high quality experience by upholding their principle of sustainability. Patrons get to choose from a selection of freshly caught seafood, and their dishes are prepared with locally sourced produce and ingredients. Their fish is cooked to order or can be purchased uncooked to take home.\n	\n                  1794 South Kihei Rd., Kihei 96753	20.735282	-156.4535162	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
29	Le Yellow Sub	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/07/19/DV3408_le-yellow-sub_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1626721010245.jpeg	\nLe Yellow Sub makes authentic Vietnamese dishes like pâté, spring rolls and bánh mì, which is a popular menu item.\n	\n                  Food Truck, 213 Kalanianaole Ave., Hilo 96720	19.7244222	-155.0609554	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
30	Castaway Waterfront Restaurant & Sushi Bar	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/07/19/DV3408_lobster-enchiladas_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1626721010411.jpeg	\nCastaway Waterfront proudly serves fresh seafood, as well as feature sushi, steak and beer on the menu.\n	\n                  1406 Ocean View Ave., Marathon 33050	24.7050304	-81.1098459	testrestaurant_state1	testfood_type1	testepisode_info1
31	Coolinary Cafe	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/07/09/DV3407_Cornmeal-Snapper_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1625849837574.jpeg	\nCouple Tim and Jenny Lipman opened Coolinary Cafe in 2012, based on the principle that restaurants are places to enjoy both good food and good company. Chef Tim Lipman supports that principle by making use of seasonal ingredients and local farming.\n	\n                  4650 Donald Ross Rd, Suite 110, Palm Beach Gardens 33418	26.8815899	-80.1072736	testrestaurant_state2	testfood_type2	testepisode_info2
32	Hilo Bay Cafe	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/08/13/hilo-bay.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1629125719833.jpeg	\nHilo Bay Cafe has served fresh, contemporary and locally sourced and inspired dishes since 2003. Now located on Hilo Bay with views of the ocean, Mauna Kea, and Hilo’s downtown area, the restaurant is frequented by tourists and locals looking to enjoy good food, a selection of drinks and fun atmosphere.\n	\n                  123 Lihiwai Street, Hilo 96720	19.7249944	-155.0704693	testrestaurant_state2	testfood_type2	testepisode_info2
33	Irie Island Eats	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2021/07/09/DV3407__Pineapple-Mojo-Chicken-noodle-bowl_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1625849838680.jpeg	\nIrie Island Easts is dedicated to preparing meals that taste good and creating a dining experience that feels good. They are inspired by cuisine of islands around the world and pride themselves on using fresh ingredients in a farm-to-table sourcing style and cooking over a wood fire.\n	\n                  4540 Overseas Highway, Marathon 33050	24.714086	-81.0852424	testrestaurant_state2	testfood_type2	testepisode_info2
35	Stogie Joe's Tavern	//food.fnr.sndimg.com/content/dam/images/food/fullset/2020/08/10/DV3209__crab-gravy_s4x3.jpg.rend.hgtvcom.231.174.suffix/1597077199446.jpeg	\nThree brothers from Philly took over a local tavern to bring the Italian recipes they loved growing up to the neighborhood. At Stogie Joe’s Tavern, the Leuzzi brothers are sharing their mother’s best recipes including her Sunday crab gravy. “It’s flavorcity,” said Guy of the sauce. They are also cranking out memorable square pizzas. The Stogie Joe's Pizza is made with house-made, hand-stretched mozzarella-layered dough and topped with sopressata, fresh tomato sauce and a sprinkling of asiago. Once out of the oven the crispy pie is finished with a shower of fresh basil. Guy called it a “dynamite pie.”\n	\n                  1801 East Passyunk Ave, Philadelphia 19148	39.9275347	-75.1660069	testrestaurant_state2	testfood_type2	testepisode_info2
